{"id": "EUVD-2025-205104", "enisaUuid": "12777aa1-7bba-3b5f-b8f7-dbf602318812", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nexfat: fix divide-by-zero in exfat_allocate_bitmap\n\nThe variable max_ra_count can be 0 in exfat_allocate_bitmap(),\nwhich causes a divide-by-zero error in the subsequent modulo operation\n(i % max_ra_count), leading to a system crash.\nWhen max_ra_count is 0, it means that readahead is not used. This patch\nload the bitmap without readahead.", "datePublished": "2025-12-24T12:30:29", "dateUpdated": "2025-12-24T12:30:29", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/88fc3dd6e631b3e2975f898c6c2b6bc6f7058b44", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/d70a5804c563b5e34825353ba9927509df709651", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2025-68350"], "aliases": ["CVE-2025-68350"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.02, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "3a61a4ec-0f21-365d-8fad-11de149b1cd8", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "9fd688678dd86e3be32a35e3b2c5cc3ef0c4e257 <88fc3dd6e631b3e2975f898c6c2b6bc6f7058b44"}, {"id": "47137ca3-9003-3c70-b805-54f13d3b3b1f", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.18.2"}, {"id": "520f0fdf-0730-315b-8a62-ccf2316fc077", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "a668e278-2fe0-3048-a690-f26a3260a5ce", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "9fd688678dd86e3be32a35e3b2c5cc3ef0c4e257 <d70a5804c563b5e34825353ba9927509df709651"}, {"id": "ac106424-42b8-3fc5-bbe7-62e50514f3c6", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "6.18"}, {"id": "e98b576b-47cb-307d-9811-e07c26109d95", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.19-rc1"}], "enisaIdVendor": [{"id": "a4085191-a34f-3508-84b2-f52cfdf5e1a6", "vendor": {"name": "Linux"}}], "isExploited": false}